            <sec>
                <title>The Portuguese side of Spanish-Portuguese North-Central border</title>
                <p>In line with the maximum, the Portuguese part of the Central-North Raya withstands depopulation pressure better than the Spanish one, although as we have verified in the descriptive analysis, the contractive trend becomes evident, as evidenced by the 
                    <xref ref-type="fig" rid="f7">Figure 7</xref>, going from more than 190,000 inhabitants in 1960 to 85,000 in 2020. With the exception of Braganza, practically in all the municipalities, a reiterative pattern of more or less abrupt losses (1960&#x2013;1981) as in the cases of sabugal and Vinhais, followed by a smooth and gradual decline.</p>
